Bai-Yin's law (Previous Lemma 4) is replaced by its nonasymptotic conterpart: Davidson and Szarek's bound. This simplifies the proof of (previous) Corollary 2 and allows us to prove the convergence of principal space.

We add a corrolary of Davidson and Szarek's bound.

Convergence of large eigenvalue (Previous Proposition 1) is enhanced by dropping condition $n=O(p)$. The proof is also simplified.

Convergence of principal space is now proved in the paper.

